linkchecker (7.7-1) unstable; urgency=low

    The web interface is now in a separate package linkchecker-web.

 -- Bastian Kleineidam <calvin@debian.org>  Tue, 03 Apr 2012 07:41:57 +0200

linkchecker (7.0-1) unstable; urgency=low

    Support for the  system configuration file located in
    /etc/linkchecker/linkcheckerrc has been removed.
    The user-specific configuration file located in
    $HOME/.linkchecker/linkcheckerrc can be used instead.

 -- Bastian Kleineidam <calvin@debian.org>  Sat, 07 May 2011 14:01:23 +0200

linkchecker (5.3-1) unstable; urgency=low

    The --password option refuses to take any arguments anymore. Instead
    it reads the password interactively from the command line.

 -- Bastian Kleineidam <calvin@debian.org>  Sun, 11 Jan 2009 01:36:33 +0100

linkchecker (5.0-1) unstable; urgency=low

    The web interface files moved due to FHS regulations.
    You have to reconfigure the web interface at
    /etc/apache2/conf.d/linkchecker

 -- Bastian Kleineidam <calvin@debian.org>  Sun, 11 Jan 2009 01:36:33 +0100

